title: Can't join Status CC Community
body:
# Bug Report

## Description

I was able to import my keycard account on Status Desktop so I am now trying to join the Status CC community using it but it fails to import

## Steps to reproduce

1. Log in old account
2. View Status CC Community
4. Copy URL
![share_cc](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/110212804/aa5650e0-cc8f-4d10-a6b4-4aa0d893a6c1)

5. log out
6. Login with keycard (new account)
7. Go to Communities -> Import using key
8. Past Status CC URL (I am not revealing the key on purpose): https://status.app/c/zQ3shf8Evh...czZkvS69P6rJ7aed
9. I can see green "Public Key detected"
10. Click "Import"

#### Expected behavior

I join the community or at least I have some indication that I am now waiting from approval from community owner

#### Actual behavior

Modal stays open with wheel of death

![wheel_of_death](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/110212804/fe7df50d-bc0e-4824-b9b9-2b6b64aacac2)
### Additional Information

- Status desktop version: v0.13.2
- Operating System: Fedora Linux x86_64

#### Bonus

When I open the URL https://status.app/c/zQ3shf8Evh...czZkvS69P6rJ7aed in firefox, I get an auth modal:

![browser](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/110212804/690dc15b-dcdb-4449-875a-0f8ca0af8389)


Logs:
